Text.string: I know a diva when I see one. That Calypso girl drinks up attention like a Zaford slurps his ale.
I never quite trusted that Aurelia lady. Now I know why. Always trust your instincts, I suppose.
Never understood the Jakobs obsession with only needing one shot. The more the merrier, I say.
That new AI on board won't stop direct-ECHOing me pictures of his data nexus. I don't even have a frame of reference to know if I should be impressed or not.
Say, you haven't been trudging through a swamp have you? Not judging, just... asking.
Those Jakobs sure love their intrigue.
Never thought the bandits could pull together something like that Carnivora monster.
Tannis always has another trick up her sleeve, doesn't she?
Well, that's one Calypso down. A pretty good start, I'd say.
Typhon's a... what's the word? A real mensch.
So... Typhon's the father of the Calypsos, huh? Family can be tough.
I used to have bars all over Pandora. Hard to keep regular patrons with the Children of the Vault murdering them all.
So long, Typhon. We'll always remember you.
You did it, Vault Hunter. Can't say I ever doubted you. But bravo nonetheless.
Oh, you poor thing.
Never considered myself a lady in waiting, but... I'm waiting.
[sigh] There's always another job to do.
Can't wait to slip into something more comfortable later tonight.
Business before pleasure. But we always get to pleasure eventually.
You know, my son Scooter helped build this ship. I see him in every crossed wire and leaky pressure seal.
Promethea's a real mess. Almost makes Pandora look nice by comparison.
Maya's lookin' good these days. Tell her I said hi.
Boys and their toys, huh? Good job taking Katagawa's away from him.
Heard you took that Katagawa prick down a few pegs. Then killed him. Nice.
Maya... I... I just can't.
Good to see Hammerlock's still on his big game.
I've got some work for you when you have the time, sugar.
Come by and see me when you have the chance.
Swing by the bar sometime. Got some business to talk with you.
Pleasure!
Toodle-oo.
Come again, when you're up to it.
Be seeing you.
Thanks for coming by.
Mmm. Ellie wasn't kidding about that.
See you soon, I hope.
I do hate our goodbyes.
Tell Marcus his tab doesn't count as alimony and he needs to pay that, too.
Don't you forget about me.
Hey there, sugar.
What're ya having?
Hi.
Look at you, brightening up my day.
Welcome in.
Got a job with your name on it, sugar.
There's some work you could do for me, under the table. And I've got a mission for you, too.
Want to earn some hard cash?
Help me out with something, sugar.
Mind giving me a hand on a job?
Morale in the Crimson Raiders was getting pretty low. I figured I'd come along for the ride and raise everyone's... spirits.
Good to get off Pandora for a bit and see how my other bar franchises are doing.
I'm not just a bartender, you know. I'm also the ship's chaplain and legal counsel, so if you feel like getting married and then divorced, I'm your one-stop shop.
Promethea might be all neon and glam, but it's got the same grimy underbelly as every planet.
Tell Rhys I might talk to him again someday—IF he gets rid of that ridiculous moustache.
Zer0's around, is he? Tell him he can come read me poetry any day.
Sordid family drama everywhere we go. Makes one pine for the days of simple mercenary murder, doesn't it?
Grabbing a quick drink before taking on an egomaniacal cult leader with the power of an eldritch god? I understand.
Saving the universe is thirsty work, sugar.
Well, you did it. You saved Pandora. How's it feel?
I knew you were a hero the moment you set foot in my bar. Be careful out there, though—heroes never quite seem to see the bullseye on their backs.
This ship! I don't know what's more worrying: that half my taps are pouring out anti-freeze, or that my customers can't get enough of it.
Nothing like a cocktail and a wink to raise morale.
Space is cold, honey. Let's get you warmed up.
You're always welcome at Moxxi's, sugar.
It's always happy hour when I see you, sugar.
Lot of familiar faces been showin' up at my bar. Reminds me of the good old days.
That little urchin of Maya's has been tryin' to sneak into my bar. I don't know what the drinking age is in space, but she's not it.
The monks of Athenas are notoriously tight-lipped with their beer recipe. Maybe I should dip down there and see if I can't loosen them up a bit.
Heard you gave Katagawa the pink slip. Slimy weirdo had it coming.
So Atlas is still standing tall, huh? Keep it up, Vault Hunter.
I heard you were there when Maya went. I'm sorry, Vault Hunter. I wish I could say it doesn't happen, but, well... none of us are with the Raiders because it's safe.
Tell Ava I'm here if she needs to talk.
If I ever get my hands on those twin vampire brats, I'm gonna wring them dry.
Hammerlock's got a new beau, does he? Hope this one takes.
Ugh. Aurelia. She gives femme fatales a bad name.
Oh, you met Clay, have you? I know a few ladies who'd pay him to read a phonebook.
If you see Clay again, tell him I said, “Mmm.”
This isn't the first time Tannis has been kidnapped—she'll be all right. Still, you better get to saving her.
Don't see why everyone's so surprised about Tannis. You'd think I was the only one who talked her clothes off.
Fancy a drink at the end of the world?
Troy Calypso got what he deserved. One more brat to go.
How's that job coming?
You still working on that little thing of ours?
Let me know when that job's done.
Not that I don't love looking at you, but... don't you have a job to do?
Once you're done with our business, we can move on to pleasure. Wouldn't that be nice?
Thanks, sugar.
Just a little tip?
Hey, I'll take it.
How sweet.
Better than nothing, I suppose.
Even a little goes a long way in my book.
Appreciate it.
Ooh. Thanks.
Every little bit helps, sugar.
Glad to be appreciated.
Keep it up, sugar, and I might have to find a way to show my appreciation.
Oh, you dear sweet thing.
I always appreciate a big tip.
Mighty kind of you, sugar.
Keep 'em comin'. That's what I always say.
You must be livin' the high life, flashing cash like that. I think I like it.
You sure know how to make a girl feel special.
Mmm, now that's what I like to see.
All that, for little ol' me? You shouldn't have.
Oh you are just too kind, sugar.
Well, I guess you need it more than me right now.
You've got to be kidding me. Get outta here.
Did you really just do that?
Maybe you are a Vault Thief after all.
Don't think I didn't see that.
Well, I think your generosity deserves to be rewarded. I've got a little somethin'-somethin' for you.
Oh, you sweet thing, you. After all you've done for me, here. I've got a little gift for you.
It'd be a shame to let all that generosity go to waste. Here. Don't say I never contributed to the war effort.
I've got a little present here for my best customer. Hope it comes in handy.
Here you go, sugar. I think you've earned this. It's on the house.
